EAT-EZY Driver App Design

Conversation with Gemini

Create an internal app for EAT-EZY drivers that allows the driver to show their earnings for a shift. Use the EAT-EZY colours of black, yellow and red. The driver can enter the delivery fee shown and the system will calculate the fee paid to the driver. The formula for that is (Del Fee - GST) * 0.75 Have a counter that shows the amount of jobs and the total of delivery fees. Have a section that includes a tip that may have been given.

This sounds like a great utility for the EAT-EZY team. To keep it functional yet bold, we‚Äôll lean into a "Dark Mode" aesthetic using your signature black, yellow, and red palette. This ensures high contrast for drivers who are often working in low-light conditions or on the go.

Below is a conceptual layout and the logic required to handle the math, including the GST-exclusive calculation.

EAT-EZY Driver Portal: Earnings Tracker

1. The Interface Design

  • Background: Deep Black (#000000)

  • Primary Accents (Buttons/Highlights): Electric Yellow (#FFD700)

  • Secondary Accents (Warnings/Delete): EAT-EZY Red (#FF0000)

  • Text: White for readability against the black background.

2. The Earnings Logic

To ensure accuracy, the app will process the input based on your specific formula. Since GST is generally 10% in many regions, we calculate the GST-exclusive amount before applying the 75% driver split.

The formula used by the app is:

Driver Pay=(1.1Delivery Fee‚Äã)√ó0.75

3. App Features & Layout

SectionFunctionality
Quick EntryAn input field for the "Delivery Fee" (Yellow border).
Tip InputA separate field for "Customer Tips" (100% goes to driver).
Shift SummaryA live counter showing Total Jobs and Gross Fees.
Payout DisplayA large, bolded Yellow font showing the Net Payout for the shift.

4. Sample User Flow

  1. Driver Input: Driver enters a $10.00 delivery fee.

  2. Calculation: * GST is removed: 10.00/1.1=$9.09

    • 75% Split: $9.09√ó0.75=$6.82

  3. Tips: Driver adds a $2.00 tip.

  4. Display: The app adds one job to the counter and updates the shift total to $8.82.

Pro Tip: We can add a "Shift Reset" button in EAT-EZY Red at the bottom of the screen to clear the data for the next day, with a confirmation pop-up to prevent accidental deletions.

To ensure the app stays fast and the data stays accurate, we should include these "Quality of Life" features:

Would you like me to generate a Python script or JavaScript code that handles the "Auto-Archive" logic and calculates these weekly totals?

Yes. GST is always 10% and does not change

Since the GST is fixed at 10%, the logic becomes very straightforward. We‚Äôll lock that into the code so the driver never has to worry about tax adjustments‚Äîthey just enter the fee and go.

Here is the technical logic and a code structure for your EAT-EZY Internal App.

üíª The Logic Engine (JavaScript)

This script handles the math, the storage of daily shifts, and the aggregation into a weekly view.

JavaScript
// Constants
const GST_DIVISOR = 1.1;
const DRIVER_SHARE = 0.75;

// The Core Calculation
function calculateEarnings(deliveryFee, tips = 0) {
    let gstExclusive = deliveryFee / GST_DIVISOR;
    let driverFee = gstExclusive * DRIVER_SHARE;
    return driverFee + tips;
}

// Data Structure for Logs
let weeklyLog = {
    "Mon": { jobs: 0, totalPaid: 0 },
    "Tue": { jobs: 0, totalPaid: 0 },
    // ... continues for the week
};

üì± Interface Breakdown

The Input Screen (The "Active Shift")

Designed with high-contrast Yellow text on a Black background for drivers sitting in their cars at night.

  • Job Counter: A large circular "EAT-EZY Yellow" badge that increments every time a fee is submitted.

  • The "Add Job" Button: A prominent button that triggers the calculation:

    • Formula: ((Fee√∑1.1)√ó0.75)+Tip

  • Running Total: A live dollar amount showing exactly what they‚Äôve made so far today.

The History Screen (Daily/Weekly)

  • Daily Log: Lists each individual job with a timestamp. If a driver sees a mistake, they can hit the Red "X" to remove that specific entry.

  • Weekly Summary: A collapsed view showing the total for the last 7 days.

    • Monday: $142.50

    • Tuesday: $118.20

    • Wednesday: $165.00

üõ†Ô∏è Data Storage Strategy

Since this is an internal driver app, you have two great options for how the logs are saved:

  1. Local Storage (Simple): The data stays on the driver's phone. If they clear their browser cache, the logs disappear.

  2. Database Sync (EAT-EZY Cloud): The logs are saved to the driver's profile. This allows you to provide them with an End-of-Year Tax Statement automatically.

Note on the Formula: By dividing by 1.1, we are effectively stripping the 10% GST before giving the driver their 75% cut. This ensures the company and the driver are only splitting the "real" revenue.

<script>
    let currentShift = {
        jobs: 0,
        earnings: 0
    };

    function addJob() {
        const feeInput = document.getElementById('delFee');
        const tipInput = document.getElementById('tipAmount');
        
        const fee = parseFloat(feeInput.value) || 0;
        const tip = parseFloat(tipInput.value) || 0;

        if (fee <= 0) return alert("Please enter a delivery fee.");

        // FORMULA: (Fee / 1.1) * 0.75 + Tip
        const netFromFee = (fee / 1.1) * 0.75;
        const totalForJob = netFromFee + tip;

        // Update State
        currentShift.jobs++;
        currentShift.earnings += totalForJob;

        // Update UI
        document.getElementById('jobCount').innerText = currentShift.jobs;
        document.getElementById('totalPayout').innerText = `$${currentShift.earnings.toFixed(2)}`;

        // Add to visual log
        const logEntry = document.createElement('div');
        logEntry.className = 'log-item';
        logEntry.innerHTML = `<span>Job #${currentShift.jobs}</span> <span>$${totalForJob.toFixed(2)}</span>`;
        document.getElementById('dailyLog').prepend(logEntry);

        // Reset Inputs
        feeInput.value = '';
        tipInput.value = '';
    }

    function endShift() {
        if (confirm("End shift and save to weekly log?")) {
            // Logic to save currentShift to a Weekly object would go here
            alert(`Shift Logged!\nJobs: ${currentShift.jobs}\nTotal: $${currentShift.earnings.toFixed(2)}`);
            
            // Reset UI
            currentShift = { jobs: 0, earnings: 0 };
            document.getElementById('jobCount').innerText = '0';
            document.getElementById('totalPayout').innerText = '$0.00';
            document.getElementById('dailyLog').innerHTML = '';
        }
    }
</script>

</body>

How this works for the driver:

  1. Fixed GST: The code automatically uses the 1.1 divisor as requested.

  2. Calculated Payout: It takes the delivery fee, strips the tax, takes the 75% cut, and then adds 100% of the tip.

  3. Mobile Friendly: The buttons are large and "thumb-ready" for drivers using phones in mounts.

  4. Instant Feedback: Every time they add a job, the total at the top updates immediately.

To make the data "sticky" so it doesn't disappear when the browser is closed, we will use LocalStorage. This allows the driver's phone to remember their earnings for the entire week without needing a backend server.

I have updated the logic to include a Weekly Log section that persists and automatically sums up the last 7 days.

<body>

<div class="container">

    </header>

    <div class="dashboard">

<script>
    let currentShift = { jobs: 0, earnings: 0 };
    let history = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('ee_history')) || [];

    function updateUI() {
        document.getElementById('jobCount').innerText = currentShift.jobs;
        document.getElementById('totalPayout').innerText = `$${currentShift.earnings.toFixed(2)}`;
        
        const tbody = document.getElementById('weeklyBody');
        tbody.innerHTML = '';
        let wJobs = 0, wPay = 0;

        history.slice().reverse().forEach(shift => {
            const row = `<tr><td>${shift.date}</td><td>${shift.jobs}</td><td>$${shift.pay.toFixed(2)}</td></tr>`;
            tbody.innerHTML += row;
            wJobs += shift.jobs;
            wPay += shift.pay;
        });

        document.getElementById('weekJobs').innerText = wJobs;
        document.getElementById('weekPay').innerText = `$${wPay.toFixed(2)}`;
    }

    function addJob() {
        const fee = parseFloat(document.getElementById('delFee').value) || 0;
        const tip = parseFloat(document.getElementById('tipAmount').value) || 0;
        if (fee <= 0) return;

        const net = (fee / 1.1) * 0.75 + tip;
        currentShift.jobs++;
        currentShift.earnings += net;

        document.getElementById('delFee').value = '';
        document.getElementById('tipAmount').value = '';
        updateUI();
    }

    function endShift() {
        if (currentShift.jobs === 0) return;
        if (confirm("Close shift and save to weekly log?")) {
            const shiftData = {
                date: new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-AU', { weekday: 'short', day: 'numeric' }),
                jobs: currentShift.jobs,
                pay: currentShift.earnings
            };
            history.push(shiftData);
            if (history.length > 7) history.shift(); // Keep only last 7 days
            localStorage.setItem('ee_history', JSON.stringify(history));
            
            currentShift = { jobs: 0, earnings: 0 };
            updateUI();
        }
    }

    updateUI();
</script>
</body>
</html>

Key Additions:

  • Weekly Persistence: Using localStorage, the data survives phone restarts or browser refreshes.

  • Running Weekly Total: The table footer automatically calculates the sum of all logged shifts.

  • Automatic Cleanup: The history is set to keep the last 7 entries, preventing the list from becoming cluttered.

  • GST Calculation: Locked at the 1.1 divisor for a 10% rate as requested.

Updated Script Logic

Replace the <script> section in your previous file with this version to enable the new features:

JavaScript
    let currentShift = { jobs: 0, earnings: 0 };
    let history = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('ee_history')) || [];

    function updateUI() {
        document.getElementById('jobCount').innerText = currentShift.jobs;
        document.getElementById('totalPayout').innerText = `$${currentShift.earnings.toFixed(2)}`;
        
        const tbody = document.getElementById('weeklyBody');
        tbody.innerHTML = '';
        let wJobs = 0, wPay = 0;

        history.slice().reverse().forEach(shift => {
            const row = `<tr><td>${shift.date}</td><td>${shift.jobs}</td><td>$${shift.pay.toFixed(2)}</td></tr>`;
            tbody.innerHTML += row;
            wJobs += shift.jobs;
            wPay += shift.pay;
        });

        document.getElementById('weekJobs').innerText = wJobs;
        document.getElementById('weekPay').innerText = `$${wPay.toFixed(2)}`;
    }

    function addJob() {
        const fee = parseFloat(document.getElementById('delFee').value) || 0;
        const tip = parseFloat(document.getElementById('tipAmount').value) || 0;
        if (fee <= 0) return;

        const net = (fee / 1.1) * 0.75 + tip;
        currentShift.jobs++;
        currentShift.earnings += net;

        document.getElementById('delFee').value = '';
        document.getElementById('tipAmount').value = '';
        updateUI();
    }

    function endShift() {
        if (currentShift.jobs === 0) return;
        if (confirm("End shift and save to weekly log?")) {
            const shiftData = {
                date: new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-AU', { weekday: 'short', day: 'numeric' }),
                jobs: currentShift.jobs,
                pay: currentShift.earnings
            };
            history.push(shiftData);
            if (history.length > 7) history.shift(); 
            localStorage.setItem('ee_history', JSON.stringify(history));
            currentShift = { jobs: 0, earnings: 0 };
            updateUI();
        }
    }

    function resetHistory() {
        if (confirm("Are you sure? This will delete ALL weekly logs.")) {
            history = [];
            localStorage.removeItem('ee_history');
            updateUI();
        }
    }

    function exportData() {
        if (history.length === 0) return alert("No history to export!");
        
        let totalPay = 0;
        let text = "EAT-EZY Weekly Earnings Report:\n--------------------------\n";
        
        history.forEach(s => {
            text += `${s.date}: ${s.jobs} jobs - $${s.pay.toFixed(2)}\n`;
            totalPay += s.pay;
        });
        
        text += `--------------------------\nTOTAL WEEKLY PAY: $${totalPay.toFixed(2)}`;
        
        // This opens the device's share/email sheet
        const mailtoLink = `mailto:?subject=EAT-EZY Weekly Report&body=${encodeURIComponent(text)}`;
        window.location.href = mailtoLink;
    }

    updateUI();

JavaScript
    // Load existing goal from storage
    let myGoal = localStorage.getItem('ee_goal') || 0;
    document.getElementById('weeklyGoal').value = myGoal;

    function updateGoal(val) {
        myGoal = parseFloat(val) || 0;
        localStorage.setItem('ee_goal', myGoal);
        calculateProgress();
    }

    function calculateProgress() {
        // Calculate total from the history array
        let totalEarnings = history.reduce((sum, shift) => sum + shift.pay, 0);
        
        // Progress percentage
        let percent = myGoal > 0 ? (totalEarnings / myGoal) * 100 : 0;
        if (percent > 100) percent = 100;

        // Update UI
        const progressBar = document.getElementById('goalProgress');
        progressBar.style.width = percent + "%";
        
        // Visual feedback: Red if under 30%, Yellow if over
        progressBar.style.backgroundColor = percent < 30 ? "var(--ee-red)" : "var(--ee-yellow)";
        
        document.getElementById('goalText').innerText = `${Math.round(percent)}% of your $${myGoal} goal reached`;
    }

    // Call calculateProgress() inside your updateUI() function to keep it in sync

Why this works for EAT-EZY:

  • Psychology: Drivers are more likely to pick up that "one last job" if they see they are at 92% of their goal.

  • Simple Setup: The goal is saved to the phone, so they only have to set it once.

  • Branded: The progress bar stays within your Black/Yellow/Red identity.

Summary of the Final App:

  • Calculator: Handles the (Fee - GST) * 0.75 + Tips logic instantly.

  • Daily Log: Keeps track of the current shift's momentum.

  • Weekly History: Automatically saves and sums the last 7 days.

  • Goal Tracking: A visual bar to push for higher earnings.

<script>
    let currentShift = { jobs: 0, earnings: 0 };
    let history = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('ee_history')) || [];
    let myGoal = localStorage.getItem('ee_goal') || 0;

    // Initialization
    document.getElementById('weeklyGoal').value = myGoal;
    updateUI();

    function updateUI() {
        // Update Shift Display
        document.getElementById('jobCount').innerText = currentShift.jobs;
        document.getElementById('totalPayout').innerText = `$${currentShift.earnings.toFixed(2)}`;
        
        // Update Weekly Log
        const tbody = document.getElementById('weeklyBody');
        tbody.innerHTML = '';
        let wJobs = 0, wPay = 0;

        history.slice().reverse().forEach(shift => {
            const row = `<tr><td>${shift.date}</td><td>${shift.jobs}</td><td>$${shift.pay.toFixed(2)}</td></tr>`;
            tbody.innerHTML += row;
            wJobs += shift.jobs;
            wPay += shift.pay;
        });

        document.getElementById('weekJobs').innerText = wJobs;
        document.getElementById('weekPay').innerText = `$${wPay.toFixed(2)}`;

        // Update Goal Progress
        const percent = myGoal > 0 ? Math.min((wPay / myGoal) * 100, 100) : 0;
        const bar = document.getElementById('goalProgress');
        bar.style.width = percent + "%";
        bar.style.backgroundColor = percent < 40 ? "var(--ee-red)" : "var(--ee-yellow)";
        document.getElementById('goalText').innerText = `${Math.round((wPay / (myGoal || 1)) * 100)}% of your $${myGoal} goal reached`;
    }

    function addJob() {
        const f = document.getElementById('delFee');
        const t = document.getElementById('tipAmount');
        const fee = parseFloat(f.value) || 0;
        const tip = parseFloat(t.value) || 0;

        if (fee <= 0) return;

        // FORMULA: (Fee - GST) * 0.75 + Tip
        const net = (fee / 1.1) * 0.75 + tip;
        
        currentShift.jobs++;
        currentShift.earnings += net;

        f.value = '';
        t.value = '';
        updateUI();
    }

    function endShift() {
        if (currentShift.jobs === 0) return;
        if (confirm("Move current shift to weekly history?")) {
            const shiftData = {
                date: new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-AU', { weekday: 'short', day: 'numeric' }),
                jobs: currentShift.jobs,
                pay: currentShift.earnings
            };
            history.push(shiftData);
            if (history.length > 7) history.shift();
            localStorage.setItem('ee_history', JSON.stringify(history));
            
            currentShift = { jobs: 0, earnings: 0 };
            updateUI();
        }
    }

    function updateGoal(val) {
        myGoal = parseFloat(val) || 0;
        localStorage.setItem('ee_goal', myGoal);
        updateUI();
    }

    function resetHistory() {
        if (confirm("Delete all history and reset goal?")) {
            history = [];
            localStorage.removeItem('ee_history');
            updateUI();
        }
    }

    function exportData() {
        if (history.length === 0) return alert("No logs to export.");
        let total = 0;
        let report = "EAT-EZY DRIVER REPORT\n====================\n";
        history.forEach(s => {
            report += `${s.date}: ${s.jobs} jobs | $${s.pay.toFixed(2)}\n`;
            total += s.pay;
        });
        report += `====================\nTOTAL: $${total.toFixed(2)}`;
        
        const uri = "mailto:?subject=EAT-EZY Earnings&body=" + encodeURIComponent(report);
        window.location.href = uri;
    }
</script>

</body>
</html>

Final Guide for the Driver:

  • The Formula: The app automatically divides by 1.1 to strip the GST and takes 75% for the driver. Tips are added at 100%.

  • Persistence: Data is saved locally. They can close the browser or turn off their phone; their weekly history and goals will still be there.

  • Goal Color: The bar stays Red until they reach 40% of their target, then switches to Yellow.
